<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 27 at 4:26AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...POTENTIAL FOR SLICK CONDITIONS THROUGH THE MORNING COMMUTE...
An area of snow will continue across the area through the mid
morning hours. Brief intervals of heavier snow may develop at
times, leading to accumulation of up to an inch in some locations.
This will lead to some roads becoming snow covered, particularly
secondary roads, bridges and overpasses. In addition, visibility
may drop below 2 miles at times. Use caution while driving this
morning and allow extra time to reach your destination. Be
prepared for variable road conditions and lowered visibilities
through the morning commute.</description>
